Community members around the South of Johannesburg are urged to be on alert after a tiger escaped from a plot area in Kliprivier on Saturday. It is reported that the tiger escaped from its cage and attacked a 39-year-old man and a dog in that area. Members of the public are warned not to approach the animal for their own safety. Video: A tiger is on the lose in the south of Johannesburg, residents urged not to approach the animal 